==English==

===Adjective===
'''yar'''

# {{nautical}} Especially of a [[sailboat]], a vessel which is [[well-found]], quick, and [[bright]].  One which is easy to [[hand]], [[reef]] and [[steer]].
#: '''1993''' ''Arr, here be a fine vessel the yarest river-going boat there be.'' - Captain McAllister [[w:Simpsons|The Simpsons]] ep. [[w:Boy-Scoutz_N_the_Hood|1F06]]

===Interjection===
'''Yar!'''

# A nautical exclamation used by [[sailors]] or [[pirates]] to express anger, dismay or approval.
#: '''2001''' ''Yar, she blows!'' - Captain McAllister [[w:Simpsons|The Simpsons]] ep. [[w:I'm Goin' to Praiseland|CABF15]]
#: '''1999''' ''Yar!  That's going to replace the whale in my nightmares'' - Captain McAllister [[w:Simpsons|The Simpsons]] ep. [[w:Guess Who's Coming to Criticize Dinner?|AABF21]]

